# textdomain: mcl_cauldrons
Cauldron=鍋釜
Stores water=儲水
Cauldrons are used to store water and slowly fill up under rain.=鍋釜可以儲水，下雨時會慢慢注滿水。
Place a water bucket into the cauldron to fill it with water. Place an empty bucket on a full cauldron to retrieve the water. Place a water bottle into the cauldron to fill the cauldron to one third with water. Place a glass bottle in a cauldron with water to retrieve one third of the water.=對鍋釜使用有水的桶，可以倒滿鍋釜。然後使用空桶可以取水。水瓶的用法跟桶一樣，但容量只有鍋釜的三分一。對有水的鍋釜使用有圖案的旗幟，可洗掉最近添加的圖層。
Cauldron (@1/3 Water)=鍋釜（@1/3 水）
Cauldron (@1/3 Lava)=鍋釜（@1/3 熔岩）
Cauldron (@1/3 Powder Snow)=鍋釜（@1/3 粉雪）
Cauldron (@1/3 River Water)=鍋釜（@1/3 河水）
